<h2>Covid</h2>
<h3>The COVID‑19 pandemic, also known as the coronavirus pandemic, is an ongoing global pandemic of coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID‑19), caused by severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS‑CoV‑2).[1] The outbreak was first identified in December 2019 in Wuhan, China.[4][6] The World Health Organization declared the outbreak a Public Health Emergency of International Concern on 30 January 2020 and a pandemic on 11 March.[7][8] As of 26 July 2020, more than 16.1 million cases of COVID‑19 have been reported in more than 188 countries and territories, resulting in more than 645,000 deaths; more than 9.28 million people have recovered.</h3>
